The paper deals with the problem of scheduling sporadic tasks on multiprocessors, which is a topic in the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The use of game theory and formal methods suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The focus on scheduling and feasibility suggests a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
